@NODE 11.1. "DDLI V1.00 -- THE FIRST VERSION"

Bug: It displays the functional hierarchy of an ENTP no matter what type
you scored as.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.2. "DDLI V1.01 -- BUG FIX & MINOR CHANGES"

A few changes and additions to QST.

Bug: When it displays the functional hierarchy of the type you scored as,
it assumes that you scored as an extravert, even in you scored as an
introvert.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.3. "DDLI V1.10 -- BUG FIX & MINOR FEATURE UPGRADE"

* Can now send output to printer or file.

* Displays scores to supplementary questions.

* One grammatical correction in QST.

* One question in QST replaced with another.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.4. "DDLI V2.00 -- MAJOR FEATURE UPGRADE"

* Randomizes question order and answer order.

* Allows you to skip questions until later.

* Allows you to go back to questions and change your answers.

* Displays output in a more understandable format.

* QST renamed as "DDLI.QST"

* Some major changes in DDLI.QST.

* DDLI.QST now groups together questions that measure for the same
  preference.

* Reads "DDLI.QST" all at once and closes it before asking any questions.
  This means you no longer have to keep the disk with the questions on it in
  your disk drive when you are running the DDLI.

* Saves a file that contains a record of all your answers. Sending me this
  file will help me make the DDLI more reliable.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.5. "DDLI V2.01 -- MEMORY MANAGEMENT IMPROVEMENT"

It's essentially the inside, rather than the outside, of the program that
has changed with this version. The main difference is that this version
stores the questions in a linked list instead of in an array. This is to
prevent memory fragmentation errors that occur from asking for a large
chunk of memory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.6. "DDLI V2.02 -- BUG FIX & MINOR CHANGES"

* The DDLI now puts a linefeed after the version string when it creates a
  record of your answers.

* ".raw" files renamed ".dar". (OBSOLETE IN V3.00)

* Added Readme.1st.

* The "wrapwrite" function in fpdio.c now takes multiple arguments.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.7. "DDLI V2.03 -- ADDRESS CORRECTION"

* Changed my GEnie address from the text printed at the beginning of the
  program, because I have quit GEnie.

* Changed my address in the documentation, because I moved over the summer.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.8. "DDLI V2.04 -- BUG FIX"

Bug fixes to make it work with less forgiving compilers than I have for my
Amiga.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.9. "DDLI V3.00 -- BUG FIX & MAJOR FEATURE UPDATE"

* Preprocessor instructions make it easier to compile the DDLI for
  different operating systems.

* It no longer asks for a seed value for the random number generator.
  Instead, it counts clock ticks to get a seed value.

* Instead of just creating a "*.dar" file, it asks you if you want a record
  of your scores created, and then it asks you for a filename for it.

* Added the "yesno" function to "fpdio.c".

* Added the "pow" function to "ddli.c"

* Previous versions failed to randomize the order of the answers to each
  question. This version doesn't fail to.

* Asks you to rank the strength of each of your answers on a scale from 1
  to 7. Includes strength ranking in record of raw scores.

* More questions. Some questions removed or changed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.10. "DDLI 3.10 -- BUG FIX, MINOR FEATURE UPDATE & NEW TEXTS"

* Fixed bug in pow().

* Used gcc's -Wall option to find and remove some extraneous code.

* Includes various text files:
  1 - Descriptions of each type.
  2 - Personality Type Summary

* Added the ability to read in a record file and return the interpreted
  results on it. This is useful for people who accidently save the record
  file under the same name as the interpreted results file.  To use this
  feature, include the record file name as a command line argument.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.11. "DDLI 3.20 -- BUG FIX & FEATURE UPDATE"

* It now recognizes that "X" preferences are consistent with other
  preferences.

* It now displays some instructions at the beginning.

* It now includes a Fidonet address where you can reach me.

* A "(G)oto" feature has replaced the "(P)revious" feature.  Enter "G" and
  go to whichever question you select.

* Added a "No preference" option.  Select "C" if you don't have a
  preference between "A" and "B".

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.12. "DDLI 3.30 -- COSMETIC CHANGE & FEATURE UPDATE"

* Instead of asking you to answer with letters, it asks you to answer with
  numerals.  0 replaces A, 1 B, 2 C, 3 S, 4 G, and 6 Q.  5 is for the new
  feature described below.

* It now includes the ability to save your scores before you finish
  answering all the questions.  This allows you to stop taking the DDLI and
  to resume taking it later without having to answer any questions over
  again.  Thus, it no longer forces you to answer all the questions in one
  sitting.  This means you can take it in your spare time instead of
  setting aside an hour or so to take it.  To resume the DDLI where you
  left off, include the name of your scores file as a command line
  argument.

* Spell-checked DDLI.QST.  The version number has remained the same because
  the questions are the same.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.13. "DDLI 3.40 -- QUESTIONS UPDATE & FEATURE UPDATE"

* Using the data I have collected from people, I have changed (and
  hopefully improved) the questions.  I think the DDLI will be somewhat
  more reliable now.

* When you quit the DDLI with option 6, it will give you the opportunity to
  save your answers before you quit.

* Added to the text that the DDLI displays.

* The DDLI now writes extra text to the raw scores file, and it can read
  raw scores files with extra text at the beginning.

* The DDLI now has you indicate your type by selecting a number instead of
  by writing it in.

* The DDLI now takes fewer lines to write the raw scores file, so that it
  is easier to transmit over the Fidonet.

* OTHER changed to UNIX in the source code, to make it clear that the DDLI
  is compilable on UNIX, and because UNIX is probably what OTHER has meant
  for all practical purposes.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 11.14. "DDLI 3.41 -- BUG FIX"

* DDLI 3.40 wouldn't read in a scores file, and it didn't cooperate with
  some changes I made to ddli.qst.  I fixed these bugs.

@ENDNODE

